- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the permutation groups of cyclic codes, which is a topic closely related to coding theory and information theory. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper involves the study of properties of sets of permutations, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may involve computational complexity in finding the set of permutations by which two cyclic or quasi-cyclic codes can be equivalent. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper may have implications for cryptography and security, as cyclic codes are used in error-correcting codes and cryptography. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper may involve numerical methods in studying the properties of cyclic and quasi-cyclic codes.
